            <biogHist>
                <p>Donald MacDougal, or Domhnull Ban Dughallach, was born to James MacDonald,
                    crofter, and Christina Macdonald n√©e Ferguson. He worked as a joiner but was
                    also well known as a piper of the MacCrimmon school. Donald was married twice,
                    first to Flora Campbell and later to Ellen Keeff. From the death certificate we
                    know Donald had at least one daughter, Mary MacDonald. </p>
                <p>MacDougal died in Creagorry Benbecula at 78 years of age of infmities of old age,
                    and his daughter witnessed the certificate. </p>
                <p>Although Carmichael never met MacDougal personally, he was told a long story
                    entitled 'Tuaireasgeul Mor' by John Ewen MacRury of Beinn na Faoghla/Benbecula
                    in December 1894 who told Carmichael that the best reciter of the story was
                    deemed to be Domhnull Ban Dughallach [Donald MacDougall] who had died the
                    previous year. </p>
